<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Sometimes it feels like I turn into a creature of pure anger and loathing. And all I can do is think of the terrible things that I&#39;d do to make someone or something pay for what they&#39;ve done. Even though it doesn&#39;t make sense. And staying angry just prevents me from getting other shit done. Its a vicious cycle that just keeps escalating, and you wish you were Thanos and could snap your fingers and make them dissapear. </p> <p>I could use some advice on how you deal with your anger issues...</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/damb85"> /u/damb85 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/ADHD/comments/bwfkh7/how_do_i_stop_hyperfocusing_when_im_boiling_with/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/ADHD/comments/bwfkh7/how_do_i_stop_hyperfocusing_when_im_boiling_with/">[comments]</a></span>